-- Russia Equity Movers: Evraz, Tatneft, VTB Group Active in Moscow
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-07-05T15:22:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/russian-equity-movers-evraz-tatneft-vtb-group-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell for the
first time in five days, losing 0.6 percent to 1,435.76 by the
close in Moscow.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Evraz Plc (EVR)  , the London-listed largest Russian
steelmaker by output, slid 2.6 percent to 259.5 pence, a second
day of losses, after UBS AG cut the stock to neutral from buy.  OAO  Tatneft (TATN)   advanced 2 percent to 197.68 rubles,
the highest level since April 3. The Russian oil producer based
in the Tatarstan region rallied after Moody’s Investors Service
raised its  credit rating  to one step below investment grade.  VTB Group (VTBR RX) dropped 3.1 percent to 5.84 kopeks, the
biggest retreat since June 28. Russia’s second-biggest lender
tumbled after first-quarter profit dropped 13 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
